OL,3,CTemperatures in Wales drop to -7.9C
OL,4,Cas schools closed in cold snap
OL,6,FIt comes as the UK recorded its
OL,7,Fcoldest January night in 15 years on
OL,8,FThursday, with a hamlet in Sutherland
OL,9,F- the most northern region of the
OL,10,FHighlands - experiencing a -14.5C
OL,11,Ftemperature overnight into Friday,
OL,12,Fmaking it the UK's coldest January
OL,13,Fovernight temperature since 2010.
OL,15,FIn Wales, around 90 schools were
OL,16,Fclosed across Wales on Thursday, with
OL,17,Fmore than 30 remaining closed in
OL,18,FFlintshire, Gwynedd, Denbighshire and
OL,19,FConwy on Friday.
